                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18000709-66-off342 t18000709-66-crimeloc345"></join>: On the 11th of June, as I was standing in the shop, I received information, that the prisoner had taken a hat; I pursued him, he had the hat in his hand before him; when I came up to him, he threw it away; I took him to Marlborough-street, the hat was hanging up at the door.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence. I never meddled with the hat, the hat was lying by me, and a gentleman said I had taken it.</p>
